From 629ed0de97fd82ef3b157639a44f589af17caafa Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: nvukobratTT <nvukobratTT@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Apr 2026 01:18:31 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 8/8] perf(TTNN optimizer): async OpModel cache prefetch
 (overlap DFSharding + cache warm)

Add infrastructure for overlapping block N DFShardingPolicy (CPU-only)
with background pre-filling of the OpModel constraints cache for block N+1.

Changes:
- TTNNOpsModelCache.h: add std::shared_mutex + threadSafeLookup() /
  threadSafeInsert() methods for safe concurrent access from prefetch threads
- TTNNOpModel.cpp: add gDeviceQueryMutex (serializes device queries from
  background threads) + OpPrefetchSpec struct
- Optimizer.cpp: declare prefetchFuture before moduleOp->walk; wait for
  in-flight prefetch before each FuncOp walk to prevent cache races

For single-function models the background thread is a no-op.
For multi-function modules (encoder+decoder) the prefetch overlaps cache-fill
for func[N+1] with DFSharding for func[N], targeting 1.3x-1.8x additional
compile-time reduction on those workloads.

Commit 7 on fix/bf16-matmul-padop-precision.
